    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-24T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-24T07:00:00-05:00" n="1034"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1034">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890E.00/140: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Diplomatic Agent and Consul General at Beirut</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-24T14:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 24, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>213. Reference my 209, June 16, 4 p.m.<note n="39" xml:id="d1034fn39">Not
                        printed.</note> Following from Farrell.<note n="40" xml:id="d1034fn40"
                        >William S. Farrell, Second Secretary and Consul at Damascus.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Decrees issued June 21 set Syrian first degree elections for July 10, second
                    degree for July 26, to elect Parliament of 122 deputies, this figure composed of
                    16 for Damascus, 14 for Aleppo, 6 for Horns, 5 for Hama, 4 for Soueida, 3 or
                    less for each of other circumscriptions. Communities are represented as follows:
                    Sunni Moslem 79, other Moslem sects including Druzes 16, Nomad tribes 10,
                    Christian 16, Jew 1.</p>
                <p>Neither candidates for deputy nor any political programs have yet been
                    announced.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
